  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A Residential Shelter for Adolescent Drug Addicts</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Drugs produce lethargy.  That means for a female adolescent that she has no motivation to exercise, eats junk, gains weight and develops a body image problem which leads to low self-esteem.  Learning to control the urge to use drugs is why the girls are at Nexus Recovery Center.  To learn to control one&apos;s body movements, use the body to express what cannot be explained in words, and feel better about yourself in the process - those are the goals of Dance To Live!</narrative>
  </description>
